The group filmed Shapovalov being dragged in the armchair behind his drifting car and at one point turning over, sending him skidding across the road.

Travelling at considerable speed, sparks can even be seen flying from underneath the piece of furniture.

Shapovalov, who escaped the tumble unhurt, said: 'I  decided to tie (the armchair) up behind my car and drag it there with one of my friends driving, and as it was on the road anyway I decided to sit on it.

'It was always comfortable but I never knew it could also be so much fun.' 

After several others had also tried surfing with the armchair, the friends are finally seen dragging it to the tip. There, Shapovalov said a fond farewell to his faithful piece of furniture with a goodbye kiss. 

